I’m so excited for you all to hear So Precarious. I wrote this song about unsteady relationships. More specifically, this song is about being the source of meaning in other peoples lives at the expense of your own energy/time. It’s not good for either party. I’ve watched partners of mine get so lost in my career ambitions and intense personality that they can’t see themselves anymore and they don’t know how to create their own drive and inspiration. Then, of course, I recognize this is unhealthy and try to push them to grow, to chase something, or to run side by side with me in my pursuits. Make them ours instead of mine. But time and again, it doesn’t work that way. I write and arrange all of my own music and I’m very proud of what I create. It’s authentic, it’s original, it’s timeless and it’s just the beginning. Come on this ride with me. Pre-save link is in my bio. 
All my love always,
Raine💧
@angelic.angles 📷

“Raine Stern is bringing a big band sound to the pop sphere - and getting existential while she does it. In So Precarious, Stern lets us in on the intimate details of past relationships, confessing how tempting and chaotic it can be to fall for someone who puts their art above all else - and how she is left with the blame when it becomes too much to handle for those who promised to love her. Cheekily referring to her own love as “nefarious” and “evil,” she bears her soul alongside a deliciously catchy funk pop sound. So Precarious is written and produced by Stern herself, and is unmistakably padded with her signature guitar prowess. So Precarious is out on Friday, January 13th on all platforms.”

Thank you to everyone who was a part of this project! I want to take a moment to acknowledge people who contributed their heart to So Precarious. Let’s start all the way back in Madison, WI, where I started my first band. Brett Walter @b_rett1037 has been there with me from the beginning. I remember when I took my first songs as a teenager to band practice and we started making the singer songwriter jams turn into band arrangements. My composition brain would never be the same. My brother Josh @joshstern418 for being my first bassist and buying me my first and only strat. I know Brett and my brother have my back till kingdom come. At this point, Brett is essentially another brother to me. @themusicofjoshcohen And to Josh Cohen, for seeing something in me, busking with me, taking me in, helping me book shows, talking music arrangements and bestowing his mastery on every performance we had together. @mieshaihm for always being able to play back whatever I sang at you. Miesha plays sax and she would come into my studio and I’d sing lines at her as I was having the idea and she’d play it back and then we’d hit record. There are so many records that Miesha aided me with when it came to writing horn parts. @officialnobodyreally Stevie for being a fellow, music obsessed friend. For having my back through a rough patch last year. Willing to be on yachts or in the trenches, I know Stevie is ride or die. Stevie tracked the official drums on So Precarious - he’s always bringing church to everything we do. So Hallelujah! Happy to have you on board my friend. Also, thank you to Stevie for rounding up his homies in Orlando so we could track this song. I’m going to tag y’all in the comments as I remember because they’re were a lot of good people involved. @klingenbass ended up getting that final bass take on SP - nailed it! @maddyvae and @elenajross for always being there at shows and singing your hearts out with me. We all know vocals are like the most important part of any song. @cesarh.tpt for helping me put a horn section together here in LA when I first moved and didn’t know anybody. I had the horn parts recorded but Cesar went ahead and transcribed them out. @lyd.wes ❤️

Already working on the next single release 👀 Which of my songs do you wish was coming out?! Oh, and that $500? The game isn’t over yet. We’re done with presaves and have now entered promotion stage for the next few weeks. Hit that link in my bio to help promote So Precarious and win $500!

But at the end of the day, we don’t promote great art just for money; we promote it because it’s great and it must be known. I sincerely believe that the music industry is overly saturated with people who don’t know what it really means to be an artist. Maybe you hate that I’m saying this, but it’s the truth. I am an artist by every meaning of that word. I am here to channel my gift into goodness for the world around and do so with excellence every single time. I’ll never apologize for knowing this to be the undeniable truth. Stream So Precarious and tell me your favorite thing about it!

So I Can Sleep is one of my proudest works. How are you connecting to this song? I’d love to know. I’d love to be close to you. I don’t want to waste any more time pretending connection isn’t exactly what I’m aiming for. I want my art to be a way to bridge the gaps in my own psyche and between myself and others. I say a lot of shit I don’t mean sometimes. I’m often cruel to myself. But my music and my lyrics always hold a pure-ness and truth in them. If you want to find me ever, look for me in the song. When all else fails, when I fail, you can always trust my music. It’s the one place I cannot, can never, pretend. 
.

I’m in constant disbelief that this is my life. That I’m about to be 25 with no album out (when I absolutely have enough finished music for it). Every day, it stings that I’ve done things so wrong. And now I see why very few people in this world give me their loyalty. Because you have to pay close attention to see the magic here. I don’t give myself that same loyalty by committing to my truth, my goals, and by surrendering to my music. I’m sick of having to tell anyone that I’m not regular. This music is different. That I’m quality. That you haven’t really seen me yet. Not just different from me, but from anyone. But I can only be mad at myself. But please, open your heart a little more, pay closer attention, and for the love of god, humanity, and art, listen to So I Can Sleep if you know about it. I’m not trying to hurt anyone - I’m desperate for connection. And this is what I’m trying to heal in myself. I’m a cool person. I get to be friends with Raine Stern. Why don’t I nourish that relationship more? If you’re in LA - I’ve got my first show post-op on June 14. Tickets in bio. 
.

I’m coming back into my power and purpose. I’m a thoughtful, queer environmentalist. I’m angry. I’m deeply loving. And I’m here to terrorize the systems that have terrorized us and this planet for too long. It’s time to wake the fuck up everyone. Because I will be putting a megaphone to these ideals that are rooted in compassion and science. Get ready. I’m about to crank it up to 11. Anyone who ever told me to put my queerness or my environmentalism aside and just let the talent speak is outdated and wrong. Keep those thoughts to yourself because I’m not listening anymore. When I took your advice, it almost killed me. I buried those feelings down and it made me sick. So here’s a big middle finger 🖕 to that. 

Raine is back.

Tomorrow at 7pm, the first song (Zodiac) of my debut EP “Welcome Home” drops. I don’t even know where to begin because the beginning of my artist journey feels like a lifetime ago. Anyone close to me would say I’m the smartest idiot they’d ever met. Why? Because the only difference between me and the charts, the awards, the world, the stars - is I didn’t drop this music years sooner when it was originally written. I’m proud of the music, yes, of course. But, and while it’s bittersweet to say it, I’m more proud of the fact that I’m learning to let go. The grief, the love, the wisdom, and purpose all pours out of me with the release of this music. When I hold my love, truth, and healing power to myself, it eventually becomes poison that makes me sick. It’s like your souls purpose is to cook food for the world, but you keep focusing on the recipe of craft and delivery to the point that your house is full of rot. The songs could never rot, for they are their own beautiful, perpetual creatures, but my well being does. With as much confidence as the sky is blue, I know there’s a world-changing amount of power in these songs, the ones still sitting in a DAW, and the ones yet to come from the stars and through these hands. 
So, come inside, I’m open arms. And to everyone with a heart that shines or hurts, Welcome Home.
